"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-world-europe-race-is-on-to-make-paris-olympics-mosquito-free\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get ST's newsletters delivered to your inbox  France reported 45 dengue cases in 2023, attributed to local virus transmission.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 322, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 0.9999999159385915, \"rank\": 8.40615819214236e-08, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 242, \"end\": 248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999722862596614, \"rank\": 2.4694244440384537e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: REUTERS  PublishedMar 24, 2024, 10:05 AM  UpdatedMar 24, 2024, 05:39 PM  PARIS-France is scrambling to make sure that virus-carrying tiger mosquitoes, a growing menace in Europe, do not spoil the Paris Olympics for athletes and fans, with millions of visitors due in the French capital for the Summer Games.\", \"from\": 324, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 331, \"end\": 338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 602, \"end\": 608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9549408743871035, \"rank\": 0.045965954223067984, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Asian tiger mosquito has made its home in much of northern Europe, including France, over the past two decades, spreading diseases such as dengue, chikungunya and zika.\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 644, \"end\": 664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Asian tiger mosquito\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\"}, {\"begin\": 644, \"end\": 664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Asian tiger mosquito\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\"}, {\"begin\": 656, \"end\": 664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"score\": 0.9999999879460121, \"rank\": 1.2053825978964578e-08, \"text\": \"mosquito\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\"}, {\"begin\": 721, \"end\": 727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999722862596614, \"rank\": 2.4694244440384537e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Climate change is said to be behind its easy adaptation to colder climes, with the authorities recently declaring Normandy in the north-west, the last remaining mosquito-free region in all of France, infestedjust like the rest of the country.\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 1056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 928, \"end\": 936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Normandy_landings\", \"score\": 0.6237989999318042, \"rank\": 0.5975675868399872, \"text\": \"Normandy\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Normandy_landings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Normandy_landings\"}, {\"begin\": 1006, \"end\": 1012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999722862596614, \"rank\": 2.4694244440384537e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The authorities have tried in vain to get rid of the insects, including by fumigating parts of Paris, a technique regularly used in tropical cities.\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1206, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1153, \"end\": 1158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.238718104260799e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But with the start of the Paris Games only four months away, they are on the clock, with experts warning that a tiger mosquito bite could destroy an athlete's chance of making it to the starting line.\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1408, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When you are sick with dengue, you will not be jumping over any hurdles,\\\" said entomologist Didier Fontenille, an expert on vector-borne diseases.\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1557, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1510, \"end\": 1520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontenille\", \"score\": 0.9999999849433153, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fontenille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontenille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontenille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The host cities and especially the Olympic Village must be kept mosquito-free,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1595, \"end\": 1610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 0.9999999999940883, \"rank\": 5.926290404307736e-12, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Health authorities have promised \\\"increased surveillance\\\" of the mosquito threat, which has been notoriously difficult to eliminate.\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1782, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1715, \"end\": 1723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"score\": 0.9999999879460121, \"rank\": 1.2053825978964578e-08, \"text\": \"mosquito\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France reported 45 dengue cases in 2023, attributed to local virus transmission.\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1784, \"end\": 1790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999722862596614, \"rank\": 2.4694244440384537e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tiger mosquitoes are happiest in cities, where an abundant presence of stagnant water creates ideal conditions for laying their eggs.\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1999, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Fontenille said dealing with stagnant water would \\\"take care of 80 per cent of the problem\\\" if there was a \\\"citizens' mobilisation\\\" to clean up even smallest amounts of water left in flower bowls or saucers.\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2004, \"end\": 2014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontenille\", \"score\": 0.9999999849433153, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fontenille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontenille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontenille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the rest, he said, repellents, mosquito nets and organic insecticides used on mosquito larvae could be effective.\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2330, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mosquito traps also show promise, using simulated human body odours to attract, and then kill, the mosquitoes.\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2442, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2332, \"end\": 2340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.899219894359951e-46, \"text\": \"Mosquito\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A variation consists of fooling the insects into laying their eggs in the trap, where they are destroyed.\", \"from\": 2443, \"to\": 2548, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biogents, a specialist firm, said it won a public bid to protect the Marseille Marina, the site of sailing competitions, with its plan to install 15 traps.\", \"from\": 2550, \"to\": 2705, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Co-manager Hugo Plan said they would be set up in April, spread over 1ha \\\"in greenery and in shaded, humid areas\\\".\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2821, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"During the Games, staff will regularly check the 80cm-high metal boxes, he said.\", \"from\": 2823, \"to\": 2903, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The fight against tiger mosquitoes is a flourishing business, with Qista, another French specialist firm, saying it had put up 13,000 anti-insect installations in 26 countries over the past decade.\", \"from\": 2905, \"to\": 3102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2987, \"end\": 2993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9549408743871035, \"rank\": 0.045965954223067984, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Researchers are meanwhile working on DNA modification and sterilisation to diminish the mosquito population.AFP  Olympics 2024  France  Mosquito  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 3104, \"to\": 3365, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3240, \"end\": 3248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.899219894359951e-46, \"text\": \"Mosquito\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 3366, \"to\": 3380, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 3382, \"to\": 3399, \"entities\": []}]}"